name: Operation.QueuePriority
desc: These constants let you prioritize the order in which operations execute.

items.name: case veryLow
items.desc: Operations receive very low priority for execution.

items.name: case low
items.desc: Operations receive low priority for execution.

items.name: case normal
items.desc: Operations receive the normal priority for execution.

items.name: case high
items.desc: Operations receive high priority for execution.

items.name: case veryHigh
items.desc: Operations receive very high priority for execution.
